Victory is secured with solid teamwork and great performance from key players in crucial situations. As the NBA Finals are ongoing, let's review some marvelous performances from the star players in the post-season. They spared no effort in gaining points as, in the Finals, every second counts. According to data collected between April 17 and May 29, 2022, Ja Morant of the Memphis Grizzlies topped the scoring with 47 points. Luka Doncic of the Dallas Mavericks gained over 30 points in nine games. (CGTN's Li Xiang, Hu Zhicheng and Matthew Watson contributed to the story.) (Cover: Ja Morant #12 of the Memphis Grizzlies celebrates after winning the game against the Golden State Warriors during Game 2 of the 2022 NBA Playoffs Western Conference Semifinals in Memphis, U.S., May 3, 2022. /CFP) Read more: 2021-22 NBA review: How did Phoenix Suns go off track? NBA Finals on June 8: Celtics secure tough home win in Game 3 NBA Finals on June 5: Warriors get perfect vengeance in Game 2 NBA Finals on June 2: Unbelievable comeback win for Celtics in Game 1